## Layer-by-Layer Lineage

### Layer 1 — Source Tables

Raw data loaded into `dbo` schema. No transformations applied at this layer.

| Table | Key Column | Notes |
|-------|------------|-------|
| `customers` | `customerkey` | 18,148 customers. Mixed date formats in `birthdate`. Names in ALL CAPS. |
| `calendar` | `date` | varchar date spine. US locale format `M/DD/YYYY` only. |
| `territories` | `salesterritorykey` | 10 global sales territories. Clean. |
| `product_category` | `productcategorykey` | 4 categories: Bikes, Components, Clothing, Accessories. |
| `product_subcategory` | `productsubcategorykey` | 37 subcategories. FK → `product_category`. |
| `products` | `productkey` | 293 products. `'0'` sentinel on `productsize`/`productstyle`. |
| `sales_2015` | `ordernumber` + `orderlineitem` | 2,630 rows. Bikes only. 1 line item per order. |
| `sales_2016` | `ordernumber` + `orderlineitem` | 23,935 rows. Multi-category from July 2016. |
| `sales_2017` | `ordernumber` + `orderlineitem` | 29,481 rows. Full multi-category. |
| `returns_data` | composite | 1,809 returns. Mixed date formats in `returndate`. |

---

### Layer 2 — Staging (Views)

All staging models are `materialized='view'` — no data stored, transformations applied at query time.

#### `stg_customer` ← `customers`

| Transform | Detail |
|-----------|--------|
| Rename | `customerkey → customer_key`, snake_case throughout |
| Date cast | `COALESCE(TRY_CONVERT(date, birthdate, 120), TRY_CONVERT(date, birthdate, 101))` — fixes mixed ISO + US locale formats |
| Title case | `UPPER(LEFT) + LOWER(SUBSTRING)` on `firstname`, `lastname` |
| Prefix normalise | ALL CAPS (`MR.` → `Mr.`) + NULL fill from gender via `CROSS APPLY` |
| Gender | `'NA' → 'Unknown'` |
| Marital status | `'M' → 'Married'`, `'S' → 'Single'` |
| Homeowner | `'Y' → 1`, `'N' → 0` |
| Income | Strip `$` and `,`, cast to `DECIMAL(18,2)` |
| Derived | `full_name` = `first_name + ' ' + last_name` (added in dim layer) |

#### `stg_calendar` ← `calendar`

| Transform | Detail |
|-----------|--------|
| Date cast | `TRY_CONVERT(date, date, 101)` — US locale only in source |
| Output | Single column: `date_day DATE` |

#### `stg_product` ← `products`

| Transform | Detail |
|-----------|--------|
| Rename | `productkey → product_key`, snake_case throughout |
| Sentinel fix | `NULLIF(productsize, '0')`, `NULLIF(productstyle, '0')` |
| Trim | All varchar columns trimmed |
| Financials | `productcost`, `productprice` already `DECIMAL(18,2)` — passed through |

#### `stg_return` ← `returns_data`

| Transform | Detail |
|-----------|--------|
| Rename | `returndate → return_date`, `territorykey → territory_key`, etc. |
| Date cast | `COALESCE(TRY_CONVERT(date, returndate, 120), TRY_CONVERT(date, returndate, 101))` |

#### `stg_sales` ← `sales_2015` UNION ALL `sales_2016` UNION ALL `sales_2017`

| Transform | Detail |
|-----------|--------|
| Union | All 3 annual tables combined: 2,630 + 23,935 + 29,481 = **56,046 rows** |
| Date cast | `CAST(orderdate AS DATE)` — already datetime in source |
| Stock date | `COALESCE(TRY_CONVERT(date, stockdate, 23), TRY_CONVERT(date, stockdate, 101))` |
| Rename | `ordernumber → order_number`, `orderlineitem → order_line_item`, FKs renamed |

> ⚠️ **`stg_territory`, `stg_product_category`, `stg_product_subcategory`** were defined as dbt models but have **not been run** in the database. `dim_territory` and the category hierarchy in `dim_product` currently read from raw source tables directly, bypassing the staging DQ layer.

