### Layer 3 — Mart Dimensions

All dimensions are `materialized='table'`.

#### `dim_customer` ← `stg_customer`

| Column | Source | Notes |
|--------|--------|-------|
| `customer_key` | `customerkey` | Natural key from source |
| `prefix` | derived | Title-cased + NULL-filled |
| `first_name`, `last_name` | `firstname`, `lastname` | Title-cased |
| `full_name` | derived | Concatenated in dim layer |
| `gender` | `gender` | `NA` → `Unknown` |
| `birth_date` | `birthdate` | Parsed from mixed formats |
| `marital_status` | `maritalstatus` | `M/S` → `Married/Single` |
| `total_children` | `totalchildren` | Pass-through |
| `education_level` | `educationlevel` | Pass-through |
| `occupation` | `occupation` | Pass-through |
| `is_home_owner` | `homeowner` | `Y/N` → `1/0` |
| `email_address` | `emailaddress` | Trimmed |
| `annual_income` | `annualincome` | `DECIMAL(18,2)` — stripped `$`/`,` |

#### `dim_date` ← `stg_calendar`

All date attributes are **derived** — none exist in source.

| Column | Derived From |
|--------|-------------|
| `date_key` | `INT` YYYYMMDD format |
| `date_day` | Parsed date |
| `year`, `month_number`, `month_name` | `YEAR()`, `MONTH()`, `DATENAME()` |
| `quarter` | `DATEPART(quarter, ...)` |
| `week_of_year` | `DATEPART(week, ...)` |
| `day_of_week`, `day_name` | `DATEPART(weekday, ...)`, `DATENAME(weekday, ...)` |
| `is_weekend` | `CASE WHEN day_of_week IN (1,7) THEN 1 ELSE 0 END` |

#### `dim_product` ← `stg_product` + `product_subcategory` + `product_category`

Denormalised — the 3-table source hierarchy is collapsed into a single flat dimension.

| Column | Source Table | Notes |
|--------|-------------|-------|
| `product_key` | `products` | Natural key |
| `product_sku` | `products` | Trimmed |
| `product_name`, `model_name`, `product_description` | `products` | Trimmed |
| `product_color`, `product_size`, `product_style` | `products` | `NULLIF '0'` applied |
| `product_cost`, `product_price` | `products` | `DECIMAL(18,2)` |
| `product_subcategory` | `product_subcategory` | Joined on `productsubcategorykey` |
| `product_category` | `product_category` | Joined on `productcategorykey` |

#### `dim_territory` ← `territories` ⚠️

| Column | Notes |
|--------|-------|
| `territory_key` | Renamed from `salesterritorykey` |
| `region`, `country`, `continent` | Pass-through |

> ⚠️ Reads directly from raw `territories` — `stg_territory` not yet run in DB.

