### Layer 4 — Mart Facts

#### `fct_sales` ← `stg_sales` + `dim_product`

Grain: one row per order line item (`order_number` + `order_line_item`).

| Column | Source | Notes |
|--------|--------|-------|
| `order_number`, `order_line_item` | `stg_sales` | Natural composite key |
| `product_key` | `stg_sales` | FK → `dim_product` |
| `customer_key` | `stg_sales` | FK → `dim_customer` |
| `territory_key` | `stg_sales` | FK → `dim_territory` |
| `order_date` | `stg_sales` | Clean date |
| `order_date_key` | derived | INT YYYYMMDD → FK to `dim_date.date_key` |
| `stock_date` | `stg_sales` | Mixed format resolved |
| `order_quantity` | `stg_sales` | Pass-through |
| `product_price`, `product_cost` | `dim_product` | Looked up at build time |
| `order_line_revenue` | derived | `order_quantity × product_price` |
| `order_line_cost` | derived | `order_quantity × product_cost` |
| `order_line_profit` | derived | `revenue − cost` |
| `profit_margin_pct` | derived | `profit / revenue × 100` |

#### `fct_returns` ← `stg_return` + `dim_product`

Grain: one row per return event (surrogate `return_id`).

| Column | Source | Notes |
|--------|--------|-------|
| `return_id` | derived | Surrogate key (`BIGINT`) |
| `product_key`, `territory_key` | `stg_return` | FKs |
| `return_date` | `stg_return` | Mixed format resolved |
| `return_date_key` | derived | INT YYYYMMDD → FK to `dim_date.date_key` |
| `return_quantity` | `stg_return` | Pass-through |
| `product_price` | `dim_product` | Looked up at build time |
| `return_value` | derived | `return_quantity × product_price` |

---

### Layer 5 — KPI

#### `fct_kpi_master` ← `fct_sales` + `fct_returns`

Single-row aggregate table. 24 pre-calculated KPIs covering the full 2015–2017 window.

| KPI Group | Metrics |
|-----------|---------|
| Volume | `total_orders`, `total_line_items`, `total_units_sold`, `total_unique_customers` |
| Revenue | `total_gross_revenue`, `avg_order_value`, `avg_revenue_per_customer`, `avg_selling_price_per_unit` |
| Margin | `total_cogs`, `total_gross_profit`, `gross_margin_pct`, `avg_profit_per_order` |
| Returns | `total_units_returned`, `total_return_value`, `return_rate_pct` |
| Loyalty | `avg_orders_per_customer`, `avg_units_per_order`, `repeat_customers`, `one_time_customers`, `repeat_customer_rate_pct`, `avg_customer_ltv` |

> ⚠️ `avg_customer_ltv` ($1,904) differs from `avg_revenue_per_customer` ($1,431) — the LTV formula applies a forward-looking multiplier that is not documented in the model code.

